nes, characterized by four-on-the-four beats, syncopated basslines, and orchestral strings. Artists like Donna Summer and the Bee Gees defined the era.", "Techno is a genre of electronic dance music that originated in Detroit, Michigan in the mid-1980s. It is characterized by repetitive four-on-the-floor beats, synthetic sounds, and a futuristic aesthetic pioneered by artists like Juan Atkins and Derrick May.", "Reggae is a music genre that originated in Jamaica in the late 1960s, distinguished by its offbeat rhythm, bass-driven sound, and socially conscious lyrics. Bob Marley is the most internationally recognized reggae artist.", "House music is a genre of electronic dance music that originated in Chicago in the early 1980s. It is built on repetitive four-on-the-floor beats, synthesized basslines, and soulful vocals, pioneered by DJs like Frankie Knuckles."], "scores": [0.9131376622545393, 0.8581280428011412, 0.8570367495024435, 0.8503601285272203, 0.8484398995456376], "model_name": "gte-small", "document_ids": ["Hip-Hop", "Disco", "Techno", "Reggae", "House"]}}